{"questionId":"22105767","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Over one year, the mean daily temperature in Mexico City was calculated to be <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>17</mn></math> degrees Celsius with a standard deviation of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>9</mn></math> degrees Celsius.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><div class=\"qb-leaf-part\" data-part=\"0\"><p>For the same year, find in degrees Fahrenheit</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-part\" data-part=\"1\"><p>the mean daily temperature in Mexico City.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-part\" data-part=\"2\"><p>the standard deviation of the daily temperature in Mexico City.</p></div></div>","markschemeHtml":"<div class=\"qb-ms-part\" data-part=\"0\"><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>17</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>32</mn><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>62</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>º</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">F</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-ms-part\" data-part=\"1\"><p>recognizing that the&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>\"</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>32</mn><mo>\"</mo></math> does not affect the SD&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>º</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">F</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>M0A0</strong> </em>for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"